<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BRF--ToddlerFalls     05-20 0164</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Toddler Falls,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toddler Survives Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 2-year-old boy fell off a third-story
balcony, then promptly got up and began walking around after he
landed in the grass with only minor injuries, his mother said.
   ``Owie, Mommy, owie,'' Julie Brown remembered her son, Matthew,
saying after falling off the balcony on Wednesday.
   Ms. Brown, 27, said she had been rushing around Wednesday trying
to get her 8-year-old daughter, Nicole, ready for school. When she
left the room for a moment, Matthew apparently tumbled off the
balcony.
   ``I don't know how he landed, but I guess he got up and was
walking around the parking lot,'' Ms. Brown said.
   Matthew was bleeding at the mouth and chin, and he had other
scrapes and bruises, but he was listed in good condition at Iowa
Methodist Medical Center, a spokesman said.
   ``It's just a miracle,'' said Ms. Brown. ``You can't believe how
far it looks from the balcony to the ground.''
</TEXT>
