<HEAD>British Leader To Address Canadian Parliament After Economic
Summit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OTTAWA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher of Britain will
address a joint session of the Canadian Parliament the day after
the world Economic Summit ends in Toronto next month.
   Prime Minister Brian Mulroney's office announced Thursday that
Mrs. Thatcher's one-day visit to Ottawa on June 22 will also
include talks on bilateral issues.
   West German Chancellor Helmut Kohl will pay a four-day visit to
Canada prior to the start of the Economic Summit on June 19.
