<1ST_LINE>r i PM-FighterCrash     05-20 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Fighter Crash,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>British Fighter Crashes On Takeoff, Pilot Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GUETERSLOH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British Royal Air Force
fighter jet crashed just after takeoff today, killing the pilot and
damaging a farm building, a military spokesman said.
   The crash occurred this morning as the Harrier was taking off on
a routine training mission, said British Army of the Rhine
spokesman Harry Henatsch.
   The aircraft plowed into a field about a half-mile from the end
of the runway at Guetersloh airfield, about 45 miles northeast of
Dortmund, he said.
   Flying debris from the crash damaged a farm building near the
site, but there were no injuries on the ground, he said.
   Henatsch said the name of the pilot was being withheld pending
notification of next of kin and an investigation was launched into
what caused the crash.
   There have been several fatal crashes in recent months in West
Germany involving American, British and French military jets.
</TEXT>
