<HEAD>Sports Council Dissolved After It Takes Blame For Fatal Stampede</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   King Birendra dissolved the National
Sports Council after a government report blamed the group for
failing to control a stadium stampede in which more than 70 people
died, the royal palace said Friday.
   The action backed the request from Prime Minister Marich Man
Singh Shrestha. A government commission found the organization
negligent in its ownership, control and protection of the stadium
and for failing to keep the stadium gates in proper condition.
   On March 12, panic broke out in the crowd watching a soccer
match when a hailstorm began suddenly. Fans rushed toward the exit
gates _ which were all locked except for one exit _ and more than
70 people were killed and 100 injured in the stampede.
   The government earlier dissolved the All-Nepal Football
Association, which organized the match, saying it failed to handle
the incident properly.
