<HEAD>Ninth Person Dies From Malaria In City</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BULAWAYO, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ninth person in the last two
months has died of malaria in this provincial capital, a newspaper
reported Friday.
   The Chronicle, controlled by the state-owned Mass Media Trust,
said the death Tuesday of Nancy Stewart raised questions about the
insistence by local health authorities that anti-malaria drugs were
needed only for people traveling out of the city.
   The paper said Mrs. Stewart had not traveled outside Bulawayo,
administrative capital of Matabeleland province in western
Zimbabwe, for more than a year.
   The City Council said last month the number of malaria cases
treated at municipal clinics in the city had soared from 50 in
October to 774 in March.
   No deaths have been reported in Harare, the capital of Zimbabwe.
   Travelers to Zimbabwe routinely are advised to take anti-malaria
tablets when visiting rural areas but not cities.
