<HEAD>118 Cars in Massive Accident, 19 Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STUTTGART, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Scattered fog caused a 118-car
chain-reaction accident on a major West German autobahn that
injured 19 people, five of them critically, police said.
   Police said drivers traveled at too high a speed after the fog
reduced drivers' visibility in a hilly region near the southern
West German city.
   ``It's the usual here. People do not know enough to slow down
and keep a proper distance (between cars) '' said one police
official, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   The expressway was closed in both directions for several hours.
   Police said 35 other accidents were reported Friday in the
Stuttgart area.
