<HEAD>Gunmen Kill Police Sergeant in Chile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile, (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two gunmen killed a police sergeant as
he was waiting for a bus in a suburban neighborhood Friday, a
military judge said. Officials blamed leftist guerrillas.
   Sgt. Carlos Gonzalez, 31, was the fourth member of the national
police slain under similar circumstances this year.
   The attackers shot Gonzalez six times, said the official news
agency, Orbe. The agency blamed the attack on ``subversive
criminals.''
