<HEAD>Cost of Falkland Islands War: $2.86 Billion</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Defending the Falkland Islands has cost British
taxpayers $2.86 billion, a government official said Friday.
   In a written reply to a question posed in the House of Commons,
Armed Forces Minister Roger Freeman said the government expected to
spend an additional $181 million on the Falklands in the current
fiscal year.
   He said the costs included construction work and maintenance of
a permanent garrison of 2,000 soldiers on the Falklands, as well as
military spending during the 1982 war between Argentina and Britain.
   Britain ousted an Argentine invasionary force from the South
Atlantic archipelago in a 74-day war.
