<DOCNO> AP880520-0176 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-05-20-88 2142EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TruckCrash     05-20 0307</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Truck Crash,0316</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Truck Rams Restaurant, Injures Five</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CAROLYN LUMSDEN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICOPEE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A truck lost its brakes and rammed a
restaurant Friday, injuring five people, including a policeman and
the owner of the restaurant.
   ``The officer told me he was just sitting at the counter and he
turned his head and saw the walls coming down and the cab of the
truck coming at him,'' said Detective Lt. John Ferraro.
   The truck was traveling down a slight incline in heavy rain at 6
a.m. when the brakes failed and the driver swerved to avoid other
vehicles.
   ``I looked to the front and saw the light pole, then saw nothing
more,'' the driver, Nelson Lopez, 22, of Springfield, said in a
police report. ``Next thing I knew I was inside the building.''
   The impact caved in the front wall of Frenchy's Restaurant.
   All of those injured, including Patrolman Kenneth Racine and
owner Gilbert Cote, had been eating breakfast, police said. The
crash apparently threw patrons into the counter and pinned Cote and
Racine.
   Racine, 37, managed to free himself and pull Cote and other
patrons from the wreckage, police said. Racine was treated for leg
injuries at a hospital and released.
   Cote, 43, was admitted to Baystate Medical Center in Springfield
with multiple injuries, a hospital spokeswoman said.
   Cote, known as ``Frenchy,'' was one of four Chicopee
restaurateurs to hand out vouchers to poor people for food at a
nearby food bank. He also was known for slipping free sandwiches to
those who looked like they couldn't afford them, customers said.
   One person was admitted to Mercy Hospital in Springfield in fair
condition. Two other people were treated at hospitals for minor
injuries and released.
   Lopez was cited by police for having defective equipment and for
not having a driver's license.
