<HEAD>Preparations For The Worst Are Under Way, Just In Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Democratic National Convention staff, trying
to plan for any disaster that might beset the gathering, listed
among its 179 bad-news scenarios the potential for Jesse Jackson's
supporters to block the entrance of a hotel.
   Disaster specialists reviewed the scenarios on Thursday with
administrative personnel from police, fire and medical teams
planning for the Atlanta convention.
   The Jackson scenario assumes that disgruntled Jackson delegates,
holding a ``Draft Jesse for President'' rally, might block the
entrance to a hotel in protest.
   Other scenarios included:
   _A water main breaks, leaving the Omni, site of the convention,
without water.
   _Five Missouri delegates report their credentials are stolen.
   About 35,000 people are expected for the July event, not a large
crowd by Atlanta convention standards. A computer conference
earlier this month drew twice that many.
   ``But we'll have the eyes of the world on us,'' said Ellis
Stanley, director of the Atlanta-Fulton County Emergency Management
Agency. ``We've got to know where all the duties and
responsibilities will fall.''
