<HEAD>Red Cross Visits To Cuban Prisoners To Begin In June</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delegates from the all-Swiss International
Committee of the Red Cross will begin visiting political prisoners
in Cuban jails in early June, a spokesman said Friday.
   The visits are the result of an agreement concluded in April
during a visit to Cuba by the group's president, Cornelio
Sommaruga, who met with President Fidel Castro, said Carlos
Bauverd, an ICRC spokesman.
   The four-delegate team will visit prisoners ``according to
standard ICRC procedures,'' meaning without witnesses present,
Bauverd said.
   Details of the visits, including the starting date, how many
prisoners would be registered and which prisons would be visited,
have yet to be worked out and will be announced later, he said.
</TEXT>
