<HEAD>UNITA Report Killing 51 Government Soldiers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rebels fighting Angola's Marxist
government said Friday they killed 51 soldiers in four provinces
last week and captured large quantities of arms.
   The National Union for the Total Independence of Angola said in
a statement distributed in the Portuguese capital that it made the
attacks on army positions May 10-15 in the Angolan provinces of
