<HEAD>Two Killed in Helicopter Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTLAND, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. Army helicopter on a training
exercise crashed Friday just outside the city limits in an open
field, killing both men aboard, authorities said.
   The helicopter, assigned to the 1st Special Operations Command
headquartered at Fort Bragg, N.C., went down about 2 p.m. CDT near
a residential area on the city's outskirts, officials said.
   No one else was injured, said police Sgt. John Kerley.
   Army officials were investigating the cause of the accident,
said Capt. Anthony Lascano, a spokesman at the Fort Campbell, Ky.,
Army base, about 60 miles to the east on the Tennessee-Kentucky
border.
   The identities of the men who were killed were being withheld
pending notification of relatives, Lascano said.
   He said no other details were available.
