<HEAD>Sweepstakes Island: A Dubious Prize</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rat Island, a 25-acre plot
swallowed each night by the sea, may be a white elephant to whoever
wins it in a lottery.
   The MTV sweepstakes winner ``can go there, put up a flag and
say, `I am the owner,'' said Justo Mendez, secretary of Puerto
Rico's Department of Natural Resources. ``But at 6 p.m. _ high tide
_ he'll have to leave because the sea washes over most of the cay.''
   He said conservation laws prevent development but Rat Island is
valued at $250,000.
   The promotion by MTV, a U.S. music television channel, was
announced last week by singer Cyndi Lauper at a New York City
restaurant. The winner will be selected in July.
