<2ND_LINE>AM-Bathtub Ordeal,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Elderly Woman Stuck 10 Days in Bathtub Rescued</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An 84-year-old woman trapped 10 days in her
bathtub after a fall was in critical condition Friday after being
rescued, police said.
   Ariadna Lohmann was in the critical care unit of Midway Hospital
and unresponsive, said hospital spokeswoman Judy Parker.
   Sgt. Al Pesanti said the woman suffered a broken leg.
   Neighbors became concerned whennewspapers and mail began to pile
up outside Lohmann's home. They summoned police Thursday night.
   Officers found lights on and a radio playing, but got no
response when they knocked on the door at 8:45 p.m. They kicked the
door in and found the woman lying on her left side in the tub,
which contained no water, Sgt. Len Hundshamer said.
   ``She was very weak and dehydrated. She could talk weakly to
officers,'' Pesanti said.
   ``Police have been to her house in the past. She has fallen down
and can't get up,'' Pesanti said. ``She's kind of heavyset,'' he
said.
