million Thursday morning.
   The government reported today that consumer prices rose 0.4
percent in April. Although that level was widely anticipated by
economists and traders, it substantiated some anxiety about
inflation that has been haunting the market.
   As with other recent sessions, NYSE volume was partly inflated
by trading strategies aimed at capturing dividends of selected
stocks. The Big Board's most active issue was a dividend trade,
