<TEXT>
   Scriptwriters and producers will meet with a
federal mediator next week in an attempt to resume talks in the
11-week-old writers strike that has crippled the entertainment
industry.
   ``The chief negotiatiors have been exploring a possible solution
to the impasse and feel a meeting at this time is in order,'' a
joint statement from the writers and producers said Thursday. Both
sides refused further comment.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A congressional subcommittee is trying to
determine if $6.5 million that Northrop Corp. invested in a hotel
project in Korea was actually intended to influence sales of the
company's ill-fated F-20 jet fighter.
   Disclosure of the panel's investigations came Thursday from a
committee aide.
   A Northrop spokesman denied any violation of the Foreign Corrupt
Practices act, and portrayed the company a victim of fraud by its
Korean partner in the deal.
</TEXT>
